    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MuTA43">
<l>ciṉamā matakaḷiṟṟiṉ ṟiṇmaruppaic cāyttup</l>
<l>puṉamēya pūmi yataṉait – taṉamākap</l>
<l>pērakalat tuḷḷoṭukkum pērāra mārpaṉā</l>
<l>rōrakalat tuḷḷa tulaku</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The world is inside the unique chest of the one</l>
<l>with big garlands on his breast, who restrained inside</l> 
<l>[his] great chest as a gift the earth<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">In pūmiyataṉai the extension with -atu is purely metrical and perhaps slightly emphatic, a standard feature in middle Tamil.</note>, covered in fields,</l> 
<l>having bent the firm tusk of the angry big rutting bull elephant.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
